WEBVTT

00:26.444 --> 00:29.697
<i>[Narrator]
Mutation‒ it is the key
to our evolution.</i>

00:29.780 --> 00:32.950
<i>It has enabled us to evolve
from a single-celled organism...</i>

00:33.034 --> 00:35.494
<i>into the dominant species
on the planet.</i>

00:35.578 --> 00:39.957
<i>This process is slow,
normally taking thousands
and thousands of years.</i>

00:40.041 --> 00:44.128
<i>But every few hundred millennia,
evolution leaps forward.</i>

01:39.517 --> 01:42.186
<i>[Men Shouting]</i>

02:36.448 --> 02:39.410
[ Shouting In
Eastern European Language ]

02:54.049 --> 02:56.552
<i>[ Woman Screaming]</i>

03:35.216 --> 03:38.302
<i>[Electricity Zapping]</i>

04:28.185 --> 04:31.188
Niagara Falls. Up...

04:31.272 --> 04:36.568
the Canadian Rockies,
and then it's only a few
hundred miles to Anchorage.

04:36.652 --> 04:38.696
Well, won't it be
kind of cold?

04:38.779 --> 04:40.698
Well, that's
the point, stupid.

04:40.781 --> 04:42.992
Otherwise, it wouldn't
be an adventure.

04:43.075 --> 04:45.661
And when are you
gonna do this?

04:48.914 --> 04:51.625
- I don't know.
- [ Exhales ]

04:51.709 --> 04:55.045
<i>After high school.
Before college.</i>

05:30.956 --> 05:33.042
<i>[Girl Screams]</i>

05:34.793 --> 05:37.588
[ Grunting, Panting ]

05:39.381 --> 05:42.051
Marie! David?
I don't know what
happened to him.

05:42.134 --> 05:45.512
I don't know what‒
I just touched him.

05:45.596 --> 05:47.681
I didn't‒
I didn't mean‒

05:47.765 --> 05:49.767
- Call an ambulance!
- Don't touch.

05:49.850 --> 05:52.811
- Honey‒
- Just get away from me!
- Call an ambulance!

05:52.895 --> 05:55.147
Don't touch me!

05:56.106 --> 05:58.400
<i>[ Woman]
Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

05:58.484 --> 06:01.403
<i>we are now seeing
the beginnings of another
stage of human evolution.</i>

06:01.487 --> 06:04.365
These mutations
manifest at puberty...

06:04.448 --> 06:08.535
and are often triggered
by periods of heightened
emotional stress.

06:08.619 --> 06:11.288
Thank you, Ms. Grey.
It was quite
educational.

06:11.372 --> 06:15.959
<i>However, it fails
to address the issue that
is the focus of this hearing.</i>

06:16.043 --> 06:19.630
Three words:
Are mutants dangerous?

06:19.713 --> 06:22.633
I'm afraid that's
an unfair question,
Senator Kelly.

06:22.716 --> 06:25.552
After all, the wrong person
behind the wheel of a car
can be dangerous.

06:25.636 --> 06:27.596
Well, we do license
people to drive.

06:27.679 --> 06:31.642
Yes, but not to live.
Senator, it is a fact...

06:31.725 --> 06:35.187
that mutants
who have come forward and
revealed themselves publicly...

06:35.270 --> 06:38.899
have been met with fear,
hostility, even violence.

06:38.982 --> 06:41.485
<i>It is because of that
ever-present hostility...</i>

06:41.568 --> 06:45.114
that I am urging
the Senate to vote
against mutant registration.

06:45.197 --> 06:49.368
- To force mutants to expose
themselves will only further‒
- Expose themselves?

06:49.451 --> 06:52.037
What is it the mutant community
has to hide I wonder...

06:52.121 --> 06:54.164
that makes them so afraid
to identify themselves?

06:54.248 --> 06:58.085
I didn't say they were hiding.
<i>Let me show you what
is being hidden, Ms. Grey.</i>

06:58.168 --> 07:01.922
<i>I have here
a list of names
of identified mutants...</i>

07:02.005 --> 07:03.924
living right here
in the United States.

07:04.007 --> 07:08.303
- Senator Kelly‒
- Now, here's a girl in Illinois
who can walk through walls.

07:08.387 --> 07:11.098
<i>Now, what's to stop her
from walking
into a bank vault...</i>

07:11.181 --> 07:14.309
<i>or into the White House
or into their houses?</i>

07:14.393 --> 07:16.603
Senator Kelly‒
And there are
even rumors, Ms. Grey,

07:16.687 --> 07:21.775
of mutants so powerful
that they can enter our minds
and control our thoughts,

07:21.859 --> 07:24.611
taking our
God-given free will.

07:24.695 --> 07:27.823
<i>I think the American people
deserve the right to decide...</i>

07:27.906 --> 07:30.701
<i>whether they want their children
to be in school with mutants,</i>

07:30.784 --> 07:32.661
to be taught by mutants.

07:34.580 --> 07:37.291
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

07:37.374 --> 07:40.502
the truth is
that mutants are very real,

07:40.586 --> 07:43.505
<i>and they are among us.</i>

07:43.589 --> 07:46.258
<i>We must know who they are,
[ Woman] That's right!</i>

07:46.341 --> 07:48.218
and, above all,
we must know...

07:48.302 --> 07:50.512
what they can do.

07:52.097 --> 07:55.976
<i>[Applause Continues]</i>

08:14.161 --> 08:16.079
Eric.

08:18.624 --> 08:22.044
- What are you doing here?
- Why do you ask questions...

08:22.127 --> 08:24.171
to which you already
know the answers?

08:24.254 --> 08:27.382
Don't give up
on them, Eric.

08:27.466 --> 08:31.929
<i>What would you
have me do, Charles? I've
heard these arguments before.</i>

08:32.011 --> 08:35.140
It was a long time ago.

08:35.224 --> 08:37.392
Mankind has evolved
since then.

08:37.476 --> 08:38.936
Yes,

08:39.019 --> 08:41.104
into us.

08:47.444 --> 08:49.363
You sneaking around
in here, Charles?

08:49.446 --> 08:52.074
<i>Whatever are you
looking for?</i>

08:59.581 --> 09:01.542
I'm looking for hope.

09:01.625 --> 09:05.045
I will bring you hope,
old friend.

09:05.128 --> 09:08.966
<i>And I ask
only one thing in return.</i>

09:10.926 --> 09:12.844
Don't get in my way.

09:15.681 --> 09:19.226
We are the future, Charles,
not them.

09:19.309 --> 09:21.436
<i>They no longer matter.</i>

09:35.409 --> 09:37.327
This is it.

09:44.835 --> 09:46.753
Where are we?

09:46.837 --> 09:49.840
I thought you said
you were gonna take me
as far as Laughlin City.

09:49.923 --> 09:51.842
This is Laughlin City.

09:53.635 --> 09:55.554
<i>[Horn Honking]</i>

10:01.435 --> 10:03.895
<i>[People Cheering, Shouting]</i>

10:15.449 --> 10:17.492
<i>[Bell Ringing]</i>

10:23.624 --> 10:26.168
<i>[Man]
Gentlemen, in all my years,</i>

10:26.251 --> 10:28.420
I've never seen
anything like that.

10:28.503 --> 10:30.464
[ Crowd Shouting ]

10:30.547 --> 10:34.635
Are you gonna let this man
walk away with your money?

10:34.718 --> 10:36.720
[ Shouting Continues]
I'll fight him!

10:40.724 --> 10:45.562
Ladies and gentlemen,
our savior!

10:47.022 --> 10:49.066
Whatever you do,
don't hit him in the balls.

10:49.149 --> 10:53.111
You said anything goes.
Anything goes,
but he'll take it personal.

10:53.195 --> 10:55.781
<i>[Bell Rings]</i>

11:17.928 --> 11:21.848
<i>- [Bell Rings]
- Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

11:21.932 --> 11:25.894
<i>tonight's winner
and still king of the cage,</i>

11:25.977 --> 11:27.896
<i>the Wolverine!</i>

11:27.979 --> 11:31.942
[ Cheering, Booing ]

11:56.341 --> 11:58.468
You want
something new, honey?

11:59.886 --> 12:02.639
Or are you sticking
with water?

12:11.481 --> 12:13.442
I'll have a beer.

12:22.993 --> 12:27.414
<i>[Man] Ellis Island, once
the arrival point for thousands
of American immigrants...</i>

12:27.497 --> 12:29.416
<i>is opening
its doors again.</i>

12:29.499 --> 12:33.420
<i>Preparations are nearly
completed for the upcoming
United Nations world summit.</i>

12:33.503 --> 12:35.547
With nearly
every invitation confirmed,

12:35.630 --> 12:40.761
<i>the event promises to be
the largest single gathering
of world leaders in history.</i>

12:40.844 --> 12:45.432
<i>The leaders of over 200 nations
will discuss issues ranging from
the world's economic climate...</i>

12:45.515 --> 12:50.145
and weapons treaties
to the mutant phenomenon and
its impact on our world stage.

12:50.228 --> 12:53.273
<i>Many American legislators
have contended...</i>

12:53.356 --> 12:57.444
<i>that debate over mutant issues
should be the primary focus
of what is, on the surface,</i>

12:57.527 --> 13:00.530
<i>a strictly
diplomatic affair.</i>

13:00.614 --> 13:03.575
You owe me some money.
Come on, Stu.
Let's not do this.

13:03.658 --> 13:08.079
<i>No man takes
a beating like that
without a mark to show for it.</i>

13:08.163 --> 13:10.749
Come on, buddy.
This isn't gonna
be worth it.

13:10.832 --> 13:13.835
I know what you are.
You lost your money. Keep this
up, you'll lose something else.

13:13.919 --> 13:15.545
<i>Come on, buddy.</i>

13:17.589 --> 13:18.840
Look out!

13:32.229 --> 13:34.523
Get out of my bar,
freak.

13:45.659 --> 13:47.577
[ Growls]

14:50.432 --> 14:52.309
<i>[ Thud]</i>

15:23.506 --> 15:27.427
- What the hell are you doing?
- I'm sorry. I needed a ride.

15:27.510 --> 15:30.013
- Thought you might help me.
- Get out.

15:31.473 --> 15:34.100
<i>Where am
I supposed to go?</i>
I don't know.

15:34.184 --> 15:36.728
You don't know
or you don't care?
Pick one.

15:40.815 --> 15:43.818
I saved your life.
No, you didn't.

15:59.084 --> 16:01.544
<i>You don't have anything
to eat, do you?</i>

16:22.732 --> 16:24.693
I'm Rogue.

16:30.323 --> 16:32.575
<i>Were you in the army?</i>

16:32.659 --> 16:35.078
Doesn't that mean
you were in the army?

16:42.377 --> 16:44.254
<i>- Wow.</i>
- What?

16:48.091 --> 16:50.885
- Suddenly my life
doesn't look that bad.
- If you'd prefer the road‒

16:50.969 --> 16:54.431
No. No. It looks great.

16:57.434 --> 17:00.228
Looks cozy.

17:06.608 --> 17:08.944
Put your hands
on the heater.

17:10.113 --> 17:12.490
I'm not gonna
hurt you, kid.

17:12.574 --> 17:15.285
<i>It's nothing personal.
It's just that...</i>

17:15.367 --> 17:17.494
when people touch my skin,
something happens.

17:17.579 --> 17:21.290
<i>What?</i>
I don't know.

17:21.374 --> 17:23.710
They just get hurt.

17:23.792 --> 17:25.753
Fair enough.

17:29.883 --> 17:33.344
When they come out,
does it hurt?

17:36.389 --> 17:38.308
Every time.

17:41.436 --> 17:44.189
So, what kind of a name
is Rogue?

17:46.316 --> 17:49.652
I don't know. What kind
of a name is Wolverine?

17:53.782 --> 17:55.700
My name's Logan.

17:57.702 --> 17:59.662
Marie.

18:01.790 --> 18:04.584
You know, you should wear
your seat belt.

18:04.667 --> 18:06.836
Look, kid.
I don't need advice
on auto safety from‒

18:51.548 --> 18:53.550
[ Grunting, Sobbing ]

19:02.642 --> 19:04.561
[ Bones Cracking ]

19:12.777 --> 19:15.530
You all right?

19:15.613 --> 19:17.574
- Kid, are you all right?
- I'm stuck!

19:25.081 --> 19:27.375
[ Sniffing ]

20:49.958 --> 20:52.377
[ Hissing ]

21:00.635 --> 21:03.388
<i>[Hissing Continues]</i>

21:03.471 --> 21:08.476
Weren't you supposed to bring
someone back with you?
[ Growls ]

21:20.029 --> 21:22.240
- What happened?
- They knew.

21:31.082 --> 21:33.001
Charles.

21:41.718 --> 21:43.636
Hmm.

21:45.722 --> 21:48.224
- Where is the mutant now?
- With them.

21:50.977 --> 21:53.563
I have made the first move.

21:54.731 --> 21:57.483
That is all
they know.

21:57.567 --> 22:00.445
<i>Come. The U.N. summit
is approaching.</i>

22:00.528 --> 22:02.613
Time for
our little test.

23:13.309 --> 23:15.269
<i>[Man's Voice]
Where's he going?</i>

23:42.255 --> 23:44.799
<i>Where are you going?</i>

23:50.555 --> 23:52.515
<i>[ Whispering]
Over here.</i>

24:20.126 --> 24:22.044
<i>Where are you going?
[ Whispering]
This way.</i>

24:22.128 --> 24:24.046
<i>He's over there.</i>

24:31.053 --> 24:33.389
<i>[Boy #1 ] Let's go.
[Boy #2] What's your hurry?</i>

24:48.946 --> 24:50.907
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

24:57.580 --> 25:00.583
Good morning, Logan.

25:00.666 --> 25:03.503
I'd like your definitions
of weak and strong
anthropic principles...

25:03.586 --> 25:05.505
<i>on my desk
on Wednesday.</i>

25:05.588 --> 25:07.590
That'll be all.

25:13.971 --> 25:16.265
Bye, Professor.
Bye, Kitty.

25:20.144 --> 25:22.104
Physics.

25:23.481 --> 25:25.691
I'm Charles Xavier.
Would you like
some breakfast?

25:25.775 --> 25:30.029
- Where am I?
- Westchester, New York.

25:30.112 --> 25:34.242
You were attacked.
My people brought you here
for medical attention.

25:34.325 --> 25:37.578
- I don't need
medical attention.
- Yes, of course.

25:40.081 --> 25:42.583
- Where's the girl?
- Rogue? She's here.
She's fine.

25:42.667 --> 25:45.378
Really.

25:45.461 --> 25:51.342
Ah, Logan, I'd like you
to meet Ororo Monroe,
also called Storm.

25:51.425 --> 25:54.595
This is Scott Summers,
also called Cyclops.
Hello.

25:57.557 --> 26:00.601
They saved your life.

26:00.685 --> 26:03.437
<i>I believe
you've already
met Dr. Jean Grey.</i>

26:04.981 --> 26:07.567
<i>You're in my school
for the gifted.
For mutants.</i>

26:07.650 --> 26:11.153
- You'll be safe here
from Magneto.
- What's a Magneto?

26:11.237 --> 26:14.907
A very powerful mutant
who believes that a war
is brewing...

26:14.991 --> 26:17.785
<i>between mutants and
the rest of humanity.</i>

26:17.868 --> 26:19.829
I've been following
his activities
for some time.

26:19.912 --> 26:22.665
The man who attacked you
is an associate of his
called Sabretooth.

26:22.748 --> 26:24.792
Sabretooth?

26:25.835 --> 26:29.463
Storm.
[ Clicks Tongue ]

26:29.547 --> 26:32.174
What do they call you?
Wheels?

26:33.384 --> 26:36.178
This is the stupidest
thing I've ever heard.

26:39.682 --> 26:43.978
Cyclops, right?
You wanna get
out of my way?

26:45.855 --> 26:49.525
<i>Logan,
It's been almost
15years, hasn't it?</i>

26:49.609 --> 26:53.446
Living from day to day,
moving from place to place,

26:53.529 --> 26:56.616
with no memory
of who or what you are.

26:56.699 --> 26:58.618
Shut up.

26:58.701 --> 27:00.661
<i>Give me a chance.</i>

27:00.745 --> 27:04.165
I may be able to help you
find some answers.

27:04.248 --> 27:06.626
How do you know?

27:06.709 --> 27:08.878
<i>[Xavier's Voice]
You're not
the only one with gifts.</i>

27:08.961 --> 27:10.921
<i>Where are you going?
[Cyclops' Voice]
Where's he going?</i>

27:11.005 --> 27:13.507
<i>[Xavier's Voice]
What are you doing there?</i>

27:17.637 --> 27:19.555
What is this place?

27:21.265 --> 27:24.226
<i>[Xavier]
Anonymity is
a mutant's first chance...</i>

27:24.310 --> 27:26.228
<i>against
the world's hostility.</i>

27:26.312 --> 27:29.148
<i>[Boy]
Hey, no powers!</i>

27:29.231 --> 27:32.068
<i>To the public,
we're merely a school
for gifted youngsters.</i>

27:33.486 --> 27:37.156
<i>Cyclops, Storm and Jean
were some of my first students.</i>

27:37.239 --> 27:41.494
<i>I protected them, taught them
to control their powers...</i>

27:41.577 --> 27:45.831
<i>and in time,
teach others to do the same.</i>

27:45.915 --> 27:47.875
<i>The students
are mostly runaways.</i>

27:47.958 --> 27:50.002
<i>Frightened, alone.</i>

27:50.086 --> 27:52.672
<i>Some with gifts so extreme
that they've become a danger...</i>

27:52.755 --> 27:55.049
<i>to themselves
and those around them.</i>

27:55.132 --> 27:57.593
<i>Like your friend, Rogue.</i>

27:57.677 --> 28:00.680
<i>Incapable of physical
human contact, probably
for the rest of her life,</i>

28:00.763 --> 28:04.475
<i>and yet here she is
with others her own age,</i>

28:04.558 --> 28:08.020
<i>learning being accepted,
not feared.</i>

28:19.240 --> 28:21.242
- John.
- Sorry.

28:26.455 --> 28:28.874
I'm Bobby.
What's your name?

28:28.958 --> 28:32.461
- Rogue.
<i>- [Logan's Voice]
What'll happen to her?</i>

28:32.545 --> 28:36.465
<i>[Xavier] Well, that's
up to her. Rejoin the world
as an educated young woman...</i>

28:36.549 --> 28:38.968
<i>or stay on
to teach others...</i>

28:39.051 --> 28:41.387
<i>to become what the children
have affectionately called
X-Men.</i>

28:41.470 --> 28:44.473
Welcome to Mutant High.

28:45.975 --> 28:48.310
<i>[Xavier]
But the school
is merely a public face.</i>

28:48.394 --> 28:52.440
<i>The lower levels, however, are
an entirely different matter.</i>

28:57.653 --> 29:02.366
When I was a boy,
I discovered I had the power
to control people's minds,

29:02.450 --> 29:05.369
make them think or do
whatever I wanted.

29:05.453 --> 29:09.582
When I was 17,
I met a young man
named Eric Lensherr.

29:09.665 --> 29:11.917
<i>He, too, had
an unusual power.</i>

29:12.001 --> 29:15.963
<i>He could create magnetic fields
and control metal.</i>

29:16.046 --> 29:18.257
Believing that humanity
would never accept us,

29:18.340 --> 29:21.510
he grew angry and vengeful.

29:22.845 --> 29:24.805
He became Magneto.

29:26.390 --> 29:30.102
There are mutants out there
with incredible powers, Logan,

29:30.186 --> 29:33.814
and many who do not share
my respect for mankind.

29:33.898 --> 29:38.277
If no one is equipped
to oppose them, humanity's
days could be over.

29:38.360 --> 29:40.529
<i>I'll make a deal
with you, Logan.</i>

29:40.613 --> 29:44.617
Give me 48 hours
to find out what
Magneto wants with you,

29:44.700 --> 29:47.870
and I give you my word
that I will use
all my power...

29:47.953 --> 29:50.623
<i>to help you piece together
what you've lost...</i>

29:50.706 --> 29:53.167
and what
you're looking for.

29:55.252 --> 29:57.338
[ Crowd Cheering, Shouting ]

30:21.028 --> 30:24.031
<i>[Kelly]
Senator, listen, you favor
gun registration, yes?</i>

30:24.114 --> 30:26.158
Well, some of these
so-called children...

30:26.242 --> 30:30.788
possess more than 10 times
the destructive force
of any handgun.

30:30.871 --> 30:34.542
No, I don't see a difference.
All I see are weapons
in our schools.

30:34.625 --> 30:37.503
Well, that's fair enough.
All right.

30:37.586 --> 30:39.713
<i>So?</i>

30:39.797 --> 30:44.009
It's gonna be close.
A vote this loaded
is always close.

30:44.093 --> 30:47.346
What about the U.N. summit?
The whole world
will be watching.

30:47.429 --> 30:49.890
Maybe there's some way
you could use that
to your advantage.

30:49.974 --> 30:51.934
We're Americans, Henry.

30:52.017 --> 30:54.687
Let the rest
of the damn world deal
with mutants in their own way.

30:54.770 --> 30:57.189
<i>You know this situation?</i>

30:57.273 --> 30:59.775
These mutants?

30:59.859 --> 31:01.902
People like this Jean Grey?

31:03.487 --> 31:06.699
<i>If it were up to me,
I'd lock 'em all away.</i>

31:06.782 --> 31:12.162
It's a war.
It's the reason
people like me exist.

31:19.962 --> 31:22.423
Where the hell are we?

31:32.141 --> 31:34.310
Pilot!

31:37.062 --> 31:40.482
People like you are
the reason I was afraid
to go to school as a child.

32:13.182 --> 32:16.769
- I'm sorry.
- For what?

32:16.852 --> 32:19.146
If I hurt you.

32:28.197 --> 32:32.660
So, couldn't wait to get
my shirt off again, huh?

32:49.385 --> 32:52.012
<i>[Jean]
The metal is an alloy
called adamantium.</i>

32:52.096 --> 32:57.810
<i>Supposedly indestructible.
It's been surgically grafted
to his entire skeleton.</i>

32:57.893 --> 33:01.271
How could he have survived
a procedure like that?

33:01.355 --> 33:05.234
His mutation.
He has uncharted
regenerative capability,

33:05.317 --> 33:08.195
which enables him
to heal rapidly.

33:08.278 --> 33:12.116
This also makes his age
impossible to determine.

33:12.199 --> 33:14.827
He could very well
be older than you,
Professor.

33:16.161 --> 33:18.998
[ Cyclops ]
Who did this to him?
He doesn't know.

33:19.081 --> 33:22.626
Nor does he remember
anything about his life
before it happened.

33:22.710 --> 33:25.337
Experimentation
on mutants.

33:25.421 --> 33:27.423
[ Sighs]
It's not unheard of.

33:27.506 --> 33:30.718
But I've never seen
anything like this before.

33:30.801 --> 33:33.470
<i>[Cyclops]
What do you think
Magneto wants with him?</i>

33:33.554 --> 33:37.599
<i>I'm not entirely sure
it's him Magneto wants.</i>

33:49.486 --> 33:52.573
<i>[Bird Cooing]</i>

33:59.413 --> 34:01.331
Yech!

34:01.415 --> 34:03.917
<i>[Magneto]
Toad has a wicked
tongue, Senator.</i>

34:04.001 --> 34:06.462
<i>Just like you.</i>

34:13.635 --> 34:16.013
Who are you people?
Where's Henry?

34:16.096 --> 34:19.683
Mr. Guyrich has been dead
for some time, Senator.

34:19.766 --> 34:22.561
But I've had Mystique here
keep you company.

34:22.643 --> 34:24.563
She takes
so many shapes.

34:24.646 --> 34:28.233
Whatever you do to me,
you'll make me right.

34:28.317 --> 34:32.196
Every word I've spoken
will be confirmed.

34:35.157 --> 34:37.493
Are you a God-fearing
man, Senator?

34:37.576 --> 34:40.579
That's such
a strange phrase.

34:40.661 --> 34:43.415
I've always thought
of God as a teacher,

34:43.498 --> 34:47.002
as a bringer
of light, wisdom
and understanding.

34:47.085 --> 34:52.800
You see, I think
what you really
are afraid of is me.

34:52.882 --> 34:56.011
Me and my kind.
The Brotherhood of Mutants.

34:58.472 --> 35:00.891
Though it's not
so surprising, really.

35:00.974 --> 35:05.521
<i>Mankind has always feared
what it doesn't understand.</i>

35:07.147 --> 35:10.150
Well, don't fear God,
Senator,

35:10.234 --> 35:12.194
and certainly,
don't fear me.

35:13.320 --> 35:15.239
Not anymore.

35:17.366 --> 35:19.368
What do you intend
to do to me?

35:19.451 --> 35:22.871
Let's just say
God works too slowly.

36:38.447 --> 36:40.699
I think you'll
be comfortable here.

36:40.782 --> 36:43.994
- Where is your room?
- With Scott down the hall.

36:45.454 --> 36:48.832
Is that your gift?
Putting up with that guy?

36:48.916 --> 36:52.544
Actually, I'm telekinetic.
I can move things
with my mind.

36:52.628 --> 36:54.796
Really?
What kinds of things?

36:56.340 --> 36:59.134
All kinds of things.

36:59.218 --> 37:02.012
I also have some
telepathic ability.

37:02.095 --> 37:05.515
- What, like your Professor?
- Nowhere near that powerful.

37:05.599 --> 37:08.393
But he's teaching me
to develop it.

37:08.477 --> 37:10.437
I'm sure he is.

37:12.481 --> 37:14.733
So read my mind.
I'd rather not.

37:14.816 --> 37:17.319
Come on.
You afraid you might like it?

37:17.402 --> 37:19.321
I doubt it.

37:40.342 --> 37:41.969
What do you see?

37:43.595 --> 37:45.847
Scott.

37:48.767 --> 37:51.061
Good night, Logan.

37:59.987 --> 38:01.905
You gonna tell me
to stay away from your girl?

38:01.989 --> 38:04.241
If I had to do that,
she wouldn't be my girl.

38:04.324 --> 38:07.911
Hmm. Well, then, I guess
you've got nothing
to worry about,

38:07.995 --> 38:09.871
do you, Cyclops?

38:09.955 --> 38:14.293
Yeah, it must just burn you up
that a boy like me
saved your life, huh?

38:14.376 --> 38:16.878
You ought to be careful.
I might not be there next time.

38:16.962 --> 38:20.090
<i>Oh, and, Logan,</i>

38:20.173 --> 38:22.718
stay away from my girl.

38:37.190 --> 38:39.109
[ Grunts]

38:40.986 --> 38:42.904
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

38:48.827 --> 38:51.246
<i>[Mumbling]</i>

38:56.126 --> 38:58.462
Logan.

39:07.554 --> 39:10.724
Logan. Logan, wake up.

39:27.407 --> 39:30.410
- [ Gasps, Yells]
- [ Screams ]

39:42.756 --> 39:46.009
[ Gasping ]
Help me.

39:48.887 --> 39:51.848
Somebody help!

40:22.546 --> 40:24.798
Scott, grab a pillow.

40:27.050 --> 40:29.803
It was an accident.

40:38.728 --> 40:42.023
<i>- [Xavier]
Logan?</i>
- What happened?

40:43.358 --> 40:45.986
- Is she all right?
- She'll be all right.

40:48.155 --> 40:50.073
What did she do to me?

40:50.157 --> 40:53.952
Whenever Rogue touches someone,
she takes their energy,
their life force.

40:54.035 --> 40:57.956
In the case of mutants,
she absorbs their gifts
for a short while.

40:58.039 --> 41:00.542
In your case,
your ability to heal.

41:02.919 --> 41:04.921
I feel like
she almost killed me.

41:05.005 --> 41:08.175
If she'd held out any longer,
she could have.

41:19.519 --> 41:21.438
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

42:03.688 --> 42:06.900
How are we feeling,
Senator?
Advanced, I hope.

42:08.777 --> 42:10.737
Hmm.

42:24.501 --> 42:26.920
What the hell
have you done to me?

42:27.003 --> 42:31.049
Senator,
this is pointless.
Where would you go?

42:31.132 --> 42:33.760
Who would take you in
now that you're one of us?

42:43.436 --> 42:45.981
[Yells]

43:17.345 --> 43:19.139
[ Growls]

43:30.400 --> 43:34.821
<i>Tommy, let it go!
Tommy, please let it go!</i>

43:34.904 --> 43:36.865
I'm telling Mommy.

43:51.212 --> 43:53.882
<i>[Boy]
Is that a mutant?</i>

43:59.054 --> 44:00.972
<i>[ Woman On TV]
...of this week's U.N. summit.</i>

44:01.056 --> 44:03.475
<i>With the leaders
of over 200 nations attending,</i>

44:03.558 --> 44:06.478
<i>the Secret Service
has transformed Ellis Island...</i>

44:06.561 --> 44:10.023
<i>into a veritable Fort Knox
for tomorrow night's
opening gala.</i>

44:10.106 --> 44:13.735
<i>Ellis Island rests
less than one mile
from the shores of Manhattan.</i>

44:15.320 --> 44:17.238
<i>[Bobby]
Rogue.</i>

44:17.322 --> 44:21.201
Bobby.
Rogue, what did you do?

44:22.577 --> 44:24.579
They say that you're
stealing other mutants' powers.

44:24.663 --> 44:26.665
No, no.
I borrowed his powers.

44:26.748 --> 44:30.043
You never use your power
against another mutant.

44:32.128 --> 44:34.589
I had no choice.

44:34.673 --> 44:36.716
No, you have
to understand me.
If I were you,

44:36.800 --> 44:39.260
I'd get myself out of here.

44:41.680 --> 44:45.558
What do you mean?
Listen,
the students are freaked.

44:45.642 --> 44:48.603
Professor Xavier's furious.
I don't know what he'll do
with you.

44:52.232 --> 44:54.901
I think it'll be easier
on your own.

45:00.824 --> 45:03.076
You should go.

45:26.307 --> 45:28.268
<i>[Xavier]
What are you
looking for, Eric?</i>

45:28.351 --> 45:33.231
It's strange. There are
more powerful mutants
out there.

45:33.314 --> 45:35.483
Why should this one
be so important to him?

45:35.567 --> 45:37.944
Maybe it's his way
with people.
<i>You don't like him.</i>

45:39.404 --> 45:42.991
- How could you tell?
- Well, I am psychic, you know.

45:44.409 --> 45:46.286
- Where is she?
- Who?

45:46.369 --> 45:48.329
Rogue.

45:48.413 --> 45:50.331
She's gone.

45:54.878 --> 45:57.505
<i>[ Woman's Voice]
Welcome, Professor.</i>

46:00.341 --> 46:02.635
Welcome to Cerebro.

46:07.182 --> 46:10.810
<i>This certainly is
a big, round room.</i>

46:10.894 --> 46:14.481
<i>The brain waves of mutants
are different from average
human beings.</i>

46:14.564 --> 46:16.483
This device amplifies
my power,

46:16.566 --> 46:19.277
allowing me to locate mutants
across great distances.

46:19.360 --> 46:22.322
That's how I intend
to find Rogue.

46:22.405 --> 46:25.366
Why don't you just use it
to find Magneto?
<i>I've been trying.</i>

46:25.450 --> 46:29.120
But he seems to have found
some way to shield himself
from it.

46:29.204 --> 46:32.457
How would he know
how to do that?

46:32.540 --> 46:35.585
Because he
helped me build it.

46:35.668 --> 46:38.213
Now, if you'll excuse me.

46:50.266 --> 46:52.685
Have you ever‒

46:52.769 --> 46:54.979
Used Cerebro?

46:55.063 --> 46:58.608
No. It takes
a degree of control,

46:58.691 --> 47:02.320
and, uh,
for someone like me, it's‒

47:02.403 --> 47:04.364
Dangerous.

47:07.242 --> 47:10.620
<i>[ Telepathic Voices
Low, Distinct]</i>

47:41.860 --> 47:45.071
<i>[Man Over P.A. ]
...now boarding on track four.</i>

47:48.741 --> 47:51.369
She's at the train station.
<i>[Logan]
Where is it?</i>

47:51.452 --> 47:54.706
<i>A few miles west of here.
Logan, you can't leave
the mansion.</i>

47:54.789 --> 47:59.043
- It's just the opportunity
Magneto needs.
- I'm the reason she took off.

47:59.127 --> 48:03.298
- We had a deal.
- She's all right.
She's just upset.

48:03.381 --> 48:05.633
Storm, Cyclops, find her.
See if you can talk to her.

48:15.894 --> 48:19.314
What?
Where's
my motorcycle?

48:56.059 --> 48:58.186
<i>[Logan]
Hey, kid.</i>

49:12.951 --> 49:14.869
I'm sorry
about last night.

49:16.371 --> 49:18.331
Me too.

49:20.249 --> 49:25.630
- You running again?
- I heard the professor
was mad at me.

49:25.713 --> 49:29.884
- Well, who told you that?
- A boy at school.

49:29.968 --> 49:33.388
When's the last time you saw her?
She was supposed to
meet me for lunch.

49:39.102 --> 49:42.105
You look around.
I'll check with
the ticket agent.

49:55.576 --> 49:57.537
<i>Welcome, Professor.</i>

50:22.520 --> 50:26.733
- You think I should go back.
- No, I think you should
follow your instincts.

50:32.697 --> 50:35.324
The first boy I ever kissed...

50:35.408 --> 50:38.953
ended up in a coma
for three weeks.

50:41.164 --> 50:43.750
I can still feel him
inside my head.

50:46.127 --> 50:48.463
And it's the same
with you.

51:15.156 --> 51:19.452
There's not many people
that'll understand what
you're going through,

51:19.535 --> 51:23.748
but I think this guy's
Xavier's one of them.

51:23.831 --> 51:27.126
He seems to genuinely
wanna help you,

51:27.210 --> 51:29.504
and that's
a rare thing...

51:31.089 --> 51:33.341
for people like us.

51:39.013 --> 51:42.016
[ Train Rumbles]

51:44.519 --> 51:47.105
So, what do you say?

51:47.188 --> 51:50.483
<i>Give these geeks
one more shot?</i>

51:52.068 --> 51:53.986
Come on.
I'll take care of you.

51:56.656 --> 51:59.617
- You promise?
- Yeah.

51:59.700 --> 52:01.661
Yeah, I promise.

52:14.882 --> 52:16.884
Come along now.

52:18.719 --> 52:22.140
She's about 17.
Uh, my height.

52:22.223 --> 52:25.351
Has brown hair,
and she‒

52:25.434 --> 52:27.353
[ Growls]

52:31.732 --> 52:34.735
[ Growls ]
Scream for me.

52:34.819 --> 52:37.071
[ Gasping ]

53:00.761 --> 53:02.930
[ Roars]

53:19.822 --> 53:22.617
- Quit playing around.
- [ Growls]

53:22.700 --> 53:24.410
[ Rumbling ]

53:28.247 --> 53:30.208
<i>[ Woman Screaming]</i>

53:30.291 --> 53:32.793
[ Electricity Zapping ]

54:04.158 --> 54:06.452
You must be Wolverine.

54:08.162 --> 54:11.832
That remarkable metal
doesn't run through
your entire body, does it?

54:24.345 --> 54:27.348
<i>Stop! Stop it!</i>

54:27.431 --> 54:30.309
<i>What the hell
do you want with me?</i>

54:30.393 --> 54:34.647
You? My dear boy,
whoever said I wanted you?

54:56.210 --> 54:58.129
Young people.

55:02.216 --> 55:04.343
<i>[Sirens Wailing]</i>

55:09.890 --> 55:12.059
<i>[Man]
All right, hold it.
Hold it right there.</i>

55:12.143 --> 55:15.229
Stay where you are.
Put your hands
over your heads now.

55:47.762 --> 55:51.265
<i>You Homo sapiens
and your guns.</i>

55:55.102 --> 55:57.605
- That's enough, Eric.
- Let them go.

56:03.069 --> 56:06.197
Why not come out where
I can see you, Charles?

56:09.325 --> 56:11.243
- What do you‒
- Want her for?

56:12.286 --> 56:15.247
Can't you read my mind?

56:16.707 --> 56:20.378
What now?
Save the girl?

56:20.461 --> 56:24.965
You'll have
to kill me, Charles.
And what will that accomplish?

56:25.049 --> 56:28.928
Let them pass that law. They'll
have you in chains with a number
burned into your forehead.

56:29.011 --> 56:31.222
- It won't be‒
- That way.

56:31.305 --> 56:33.474
Then kill me
and find out.

56:36.143 --> 56:39.271
<i>Huh? Then release me.</i>

56:47.488 --> 56:49.448
Fine.

56:55.704 --> 56:57.832
<i>- [Gunshot]</i>
- [ Crowd Gasping, Screaming ]

57:02.420 --> 57:04.755
Care to press your luck,
Charles?

57:04.839 --> 57:07.675
[ Guns Cocking ]

57:09.343 --> 57:13.013
- I don't think
I can stop them all.
- [ Grunting ]

57:27.361 --> 57:29.405
Still unwilling
to make sacrifices.

57:29.488 --> 57:32.575
<i>That's what
makes you weak.</i>

57:44.336 --> 57:46.881
Good-bye, Charles.

58:16.911 --> 58:18.370
You said he wanted me.

58:18.579 --> 58:20.372
<i>I made a terrible mistake.</i>

58:20.456 --> 58:23.959
<i>His helmet
was somehow designed
to block my telepathy.</i>

58:25.544 --> 58:28.881
I couldn't see
what he was after
till it was too late.

58:28.964 --> 58:31.091
Where are you going?
I'm gonna find her.

58:31.175 --> 58:34.303
How?
The traditional way.
Look.

58:37.640 --> 58:40.142
Logan, you can't
do this alone.

58:40.226 --> 58:43.187
Who's gonna help me?
You? So far you've
all done a bang-up job.

58:43.270 --> 58:45.523
Then help us.
Fight with us.

58:45.606 --> 58:48.359
Fight with you?
What, join the team?
Be an X-Man?

58:48.442 --> 58:51.195
Who the hell
do you think you are?
You're a mutant.

58:51.278 --> 58:54.323
The whole world out there
is full of people
that hate and fear you.

58:54.406 --> 58:58.118
And you're wasting your time
trying to protect 'em?
I got better things to do.

58:58.202 --> 59:02.665
You know,
Magneto's right.
There's a war coming.

59:02.748 --> 59:06.961
- You sure
you're on the right side?
- At least I've chosen a side.

59:14.718 --> 59:18.347
I'm looking
for Dr.Jean Grey.

59:26.981 --> 59:29.400
Senator Kelly.

59:29.483 --> 59:31.860
I'm Professor
Charles Xavier.

59:33.779 --> 59:37.908
I was afraid if I went
to a hospital, they would‒

59:37.992 --> 59:40.035
Treat you like a mutant?

59:42.121 --> 59:46.041
We're not what you think.
Not all of us.

59:46.125 --> 59:49.962
Tell it to the ones
who did this to me.

59:54.383 --> 59:56.343
Senator...

01:00:01.015 --> 01:00:04.518
I want you to try and relax.

01:00:07.479 --> 01:00:09.398
I'm not going
to hurt you.

01:01:01.659 --> 01:01:04.745
Welcome to the future,

01:01:04.828 --> 01:01:06.747
brother.

01:01:12.878 --> 01:01:17.007
The machine emits radiation
that triggers mutation
in ordinary human beings.

01:01:17.091 --> 01:01:19.176
But the mutation
is unnatural.

01:01:19.259 --> 01:01:21.887
Kelly's body
is rejecting it.
His cells began...

01:01:21.970 --> 01:01:24.306
<i>to break down
almost immediately.</i>

01:01:24.390 --> 01:01:27.267
- What effect does radiation
have on mutants?
- There appears to be none.

01:01:27.351 --> 01:01:31.188
But I fear it will seriously
harm any normal person
exposed to it.

01:01:31.271 --> 01:01:35.150
- So what does Magneto
want with Rogue?
- I don't know.

01:01:37.319 --> 01:01:39.780
<i>[Cyclops]
Wait a second.</i>

01:01:39.863 --> 01:01:42.616
You said this machine
draws its power from Magneto...

01:01:42.700 --> 01:01:45.494
<i>and that it
weakened him.
[Xavier]
Yes.</i>

01:01:46.787 --> 01:01:48.872
In fact,
it nearly killed him.

01:01:48.956 --> 01:01:51.625
He's gonna transfer
his power to Rogue...

01:01:51.709 --> 01:01:54.920
<i>and use her
to power the machine.</i>

01:01:57.548 --> 01:01:59.717
Is somebody there?

01:02:01.552 --> 01:02:04.555
<i>Yes. I'm here.</i>

01:02:06.473 --> 01:02:09.476
Please don't leave me.

01:02:10.686 --> 01:02:13.105
Don't want to be alone.

01:02:14.732 --> 01:02:16.650
All right.

01:02:25.617 --> 01:02:28.704
<i>Do you hate
normal people?</i>

01:02:30.914 --> 01:02:33.584
Sometimes.

01:02:33.667 --> 01:02:35.586
<i>Why?</i>

01:02:39.339 --> 01:02:41.300
I suppose...

01:02:42.801 --> 01:02:45.137
I'm afraid of them.

01:02:47.055 --> 01:02:49.433
Well,

01:02:49.516 --> 01:02:53.395
I think you've got
one less person to‒

01:02:53.479 --> 01:02:55.397
to be afraid of.

01:03:00.736 --> 01:03:03.363
[ Gasps]

01:03:18.504 --> 01:03:21.256
Cyclops, you and Storm
ready the jet.
I'm gonna find Rogue.

01:03:21.340 --> 01:03:24.468
Jean, get Logan
a uniform.
Whoa, wait a minute.

01:03:24.551 --> 01:03:27.513
He's not coming
with us, is he?
<i>Yes.</i>

01:03:27.596 --> 01:03:30.307
I'm sorry, Professor,
but he'll endanger
the mission. And if‒

01:03:30.390 --> 01:03:33.560
Hey, I wasn't the one
who gave the train station
a new sunroof, pal.

01:03:33.644 --> 01:03:35.938
No, you were the one who
stabbed Rogue through the chest.
Scott‒

01:03:36.021 --> 01:03:39.399
Hey, why don't you take
your little mission
and stick it up your‒

01:03:39.483 --> 01:03:41.735
Senator Kelly is dead.

01:03:43.612 --> 01:03:45.614
I'm going to find her.

01:03:47.282 --> 01:03:49.576
Settle this.

01:04:27.281 --> 01:04:29.241
I'm sorry.

01:04:48.594 --> 01:04:50.512
[ Beeping ]

01:04:52.890 --> 01:04:56.643
<i>[Cyclops]
You can still hear me,
can't you?</i>

01:05:04.234 --> 01:05:09.531
<i>You've taught me
everything in my life
that was ever worth knowing.</i>

01:05:09.615 --> 01:05:12.951
<i>And if anything happens,</i>

01:05:13.035 --> 01:05:16.288
well, I'll take care
of them.

01:05:29.760 --> 01:05:31.678
<i>Jean?</i>

01:05:35.057 --> 01:05:37.476
Jean!

01:05:37.559 --> 01:05:39.853
No!

01:05:52.699 --> 01:05:54.618
Jean?

01:05:54.701 --> 01:05:56.620
Jean.

01:05:56.703 --> 01:05:59.039
Answer me. Please.

01:06:00.290 --> 01:06:02.250
I know
where Magneto's going.

01:06:55.762 --> 01:06:57.723
<i>[ Thud, Man Groaning]</i>

01:07:22.080 --> 01:07:24.291
Magnificent, isn't she?

01:07:25.542 --> 01:07:30.213
- I've seen it.
- I first saw her in 1949.

01:07:30.297 --> 01:07:33.800
America was gonna be
the land of tolerance,

01:07:33.884 --> 01:07:35.802
of peace.

01:07:40.265 --> 01:07:42.434
Are you going
to kill me?

01:07:47.773 --> 01:07:50.567
- Yes.
- Why?

01:07:50.650 --> 01:07:54.946
<i>Because there is
no land of tolerance.
There is no peace.</i>

01:07:55.030 --> 01:07:57.783
Not here
or anywhere else.

01:07:57.866 --> 01:08:01.703
<i>Women and children,
whole families destroyed...</i>

01:08:01.787 --> 01:08:04.581
simply because
they were born different
from those in power.

01:08:04.664 --> 01:08:09.503
Well, after tonight,
the world's powerful
will be just like us.

01:08:09.586 --> 01:08:12.631
They will return home
as brothers.

01:08:12.714 --> 01:08:15.175
As mutants.

01:08:15.258 --> 01:08:17.761
Our cause will be theirs.

01:08:17.844 --> 01:08:22.015
<i>Your sacrifice
will mean our survival.</i>

01:08:25.727 --> 01:08:29.106
I'll understand if that
comes as small consolation.

01:08:32.609 --> 01:08:34.819
Put her in the machine.

01:08:36.071 --> 01:08:38.031
I'll raise it.

01:08:39.866 --> 01:08:42.868
<i>[Cyclops]
Magneto is here.
Liberty Island.</i>

01:08:42.953 --> 01:08:46.331
<i>Now, presumably, his objective
is to mutate the world leaders
at the U.N. summit...</i>

01:08:46.413 --> 01:08:48.457
on Ellis Island.

01:08:48.542 --> 01:08:50.710
He doesn't know
his machine kills.

01:08:50.794 --> 01:08:54.381
And judging from what
the Professor saw, if Magneto
gave Rogue enough power‒

01:08:54.464 --> 01:08:58.676
<i>[Jean]
He could wipe out
everyone in New York City.</i>

01:08:58.760 --> 01:09:01.930
<i>[Cyclops]
We can insert here
at the George Washington Bridge,</i>

01:09:02.013 --> 01:09:04.349
<i>come around the bank
just off of Manhattan.</i>

01:09:04.432 --> 01:09:07.978
<i>We land on the far side
of Liberty Island here.</i>

01:09:08.060 --> 01:09:10.020
What about harbor patrol?
Radar?

01:09:10.104 --> 01:09:14.024
If they have anything
that can pick up our jet,
they deserve to catch us.

01:09:15.443 --> 01:09:17.404
<i>[ Whirring]</i>

01:09:28.497 --> 01:09:31.501
You actually go outside
in these things?

01:09:31.585 --> 01:09:33.962
Well, what would you prefer,
yellow spandex?

01:09:37.006 --> 01:09:40.176
<i>[Engines Revving]</i>

01:09:40.260 --> 01:09:43.263
<i>- [Engines Firing]</i>
- Whoa!

01:10:24.971 --> 01:10:27.974
Okay, there's the bridge.
I'm taking her down.

01:10:34.397 --> 01:10:36.983
Storm, some cover,
please.

01:10:55.585 --> 01:10:59.256
<i>Toad, Mystique, stay sharp.
We're not alone.</i>

01:10:59.339 --> 01:11:01.258
And you stay here.

01:11:01.341 --> 01:11:05.095
Once I give
my power to the girl,
I'll be temporarily weakened.

01:11:05.178 --> 01:11:07.180
You'll be
my only defense.

01:11:11.518 --> 01:11:14.688
[ Thunder Rumbles]

01:11:14.771 --> 01:11:16.690
Sounds like
a storm's coming.

01:11:31.079 --> 01:11:34.582
- Sorry.
- You call that a landing?

01:11:46.344 --> 01:11:48.263
The torch.

01:11:56.313 --> 01:11:58.565
<i>[Man On TV]
...within a mile
of the proceedings.</i>

01:11:58.648 --> 01:12:01.401
<i>The first dignitaries
started to arrive
about an hour ago,</i>

01:12:01.484 --> 01:12:03.820
<i>greeted with a sort
of garden-party atmosphere,</i>

01:12:03.903 --> 01:12:05.822
<i>which was designed
to entertain them,</i>

01:12:05.905 --> 01:12:08.908
<i>as the others
traversed the rigid security.</i>
[ Alarm Wails]

01:12:33.266 --> 01:12:37.020
[ Sniffs ]
There's someone here.
Where?

01:12:37.103 --> 01:12:40.482
I don't know.
Keep your eye open.
Logan.

01:12:43.568 --> 01:12:46.071
Damn it.

01:12:51.951 --> 01:12:54.454
Anything?
I know there's someone here.
I just can't see 'em.

01:13:09.010 --> 01:13:10.970
Wait!
Wait!

01:13:17.435 --> 01:13:19.646
All right, back up.
Back up.

01:14:34.679 --> 01:14:36.681
<i>[Jean Grunting]</i>
Jean!

01:14:38.016 --> 01:14:40.101
Oh, God.

01:15:40.620 --> 01:15:42.830
Don't move.

01:15:44.374 --> 01:15:46.417
[ Coughing ]

01:15:49.921 --> 01:15:52.632
<i>[Elevator Bell Rings]</i>

01:15:58.972 --> 01:16:00.932
Don't you people ever die?

01:16:35.341 --> 01:16:38.636
Do you know
what happens to a toad
when it's struck by lightning?

01:16:38.720 --> 01:16:40.680
<i>[ Thunder Cracks]</i>

01:16:45.101 --> 01:16:47.520
Same thing that happens
to everything else.

01:16:48.688 --> 01:16:50.648
[ Screaming ]

01:17:03.202 --> 01:17:05.121
Logan, is that you?

01:17:05.204 --> 01:17:07.165
Shh.

01:17:12.086 --> 01:17:14.047
[ Sniffing ]

01:17:16.966 --> 01:17:20.094
The other one
ain't far away.

01:17:20.178 --> 01:17:22.680
Come on.
We have to regroup.

01:17:22.764 --> 01:17:24.724
I know,
but there's a problem.

01:17:27.310 --> 01:17:30.146
You're not part of the group.

01:17:30.229 --> 01:17:33.024
[ Groaning ]

01:17:50.792 --> 01:17:52.794
Hey, hey, it's me.

01:17:52.877 --> 01:17:56.255
- Prove it.
- You're a dick.

01:17:57.465 --> 01:17:59.425
Okay.

01:18:01.094 --> 01:18:03.721
<i>Hey.</i>

01:18:20.571 --> 01:18:22.907
[ Logan ]
Everybody
get out of here.

01:18:22.990 --> 01:18:26.035
What is it?
I can't move.

01:18:46.556 --> 01:18:49.225
Ah, my brothers.

01:18:49.308 --> 01:18:52.395
Welcome. And, you,

01:18:52.478 --> 01:18:55.481
<i>just point
those claws of yours
in a safer direction.</i>

01:19:09.579 --> 01:19:11.622
You'd better close
your eyes.

01:19:14.709 --> 01:19:17.003
<i>[Cyclops]
Storm, fry him.
[Magneto] Oh, yes.</i>

01:19:17.086 --> 01:19:21.966
<i>A bolt of lightning into
a huge copper conductor.</i>

01:19:22.049 --> 01:19:24.051
I thought you lived
at a school.

01:19:24.135 --> 01:19:26.554
[Applause ]

01:19:29.140 --> 01:19:32.685
For those of you
who may not be familiar with
the historical significance‒

01:19:32.769 --> 01:19:35.813
[ People Translating ]

01:19:37.940 --> 01:19:40.693
Mystique?

01:19:40.777 --> 01:19:42.862
Mystique?
I've seen
Senator Kelly.

01:19:44.697 --> 01:19:48.409
So the good senator
survived his fall...

01:19:48.493 --> 01:19:50.870
and the swim to shore.

01:19:50.953 --> 01:19:53.164
He's become even
more powerful than
I could have imagined.

01:19:53.247 --> 01:19:55.958
- He's dead.
<i>- [Storm] It's true.</i>

01:19:56.042 --> 01:20:00.546
<i>I saw him die.
Like those people
down there will die.</i>

01:20:00.630 --> 01:20:04.258
Are you sure
you saw what you saw?

01:20:04.342 --> 01:20:08.679
I would also like
to thank the president
of the United States...

01:20:08.763 --> 01:20:11.015
<i>for hosting this event...</i>

01:20:11.098 --> 01:20:14.519
<i>under the lights of
the great city of New York.</i>

01:20:21.859 --> 01:20:25.613
Why do none of you understand
what I'm trying to do?

01:20:25.696 --> 01:20:31.452
Those people down there,
they control our fate and
the fate of every other mutant.

01:20:32.870 --> 01:20:35.122
Well,

01:20:35.206 --> 01:20:37.834
soon our fate
will be theirs.

01:20:37.917 --> 01:20:41.170
<i>[Rogue]
Help! Please help me!</i>

01:20:41.254 --> 01:20:43.172
You're so full of shit.

01:20:43.256 --> 01:20:47.468
<i>If you were really
so righteous,
it'd be you in that thing.</i>

01:20:49.345 --> 01:20:53.099
<i>Help!
Somebody help me!</i>

01:21:05.903 --> 01:21:07.822
<i>[Rogue]
Please!</i>

01:21:07.905 --> 01:21:12.952
<i>- [Growls]
- Somebody please help me!</i>

01:21:16.831 --> 01:21:19.166
<i>Somebody!</i>
[ Grunting ]

01:21:19.250 --> 01:21:21.836
Help‒

01:21:29.302 --> 01:21:32.847
- [Yells]
- Logan!

01:21:34.390 --> 01:21:37.101
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

01:22:29.695 --> 01:22:33.074
- I'm sorry, my dear.
- Don't do this.

01:22:45.503 --> 01:22:47.588
This is mine.

01:23:13.531 --> 01:23:15.574
<i>[Rogue Screaming]</i>

01:23:50.484 --> 01:23:52.611
You owe me a scream.

01:23:55.948 --> 01:23:58.659
Hey, bub. I'm not
finished with you yet.

01:24:01.746 --> 01:24:04.373
<i>- [Rogue Screams]</i>
- Jean.

01:24:04.457 --> 01:24:06.876
Scott, when I tell you,
open your eyes.
No.

01:24:06.959 --> 01:24:09.462
- Trust me.
- You drop something?

01:24:14.008 --> 01:24:16.135
<i>Now.</i>

01:24:30.149 --> 01:24:32.359
Thanks.
Don't mention it.

01:24:32.443 --> 01:24:36.447
We gotta get her
out of there.
Cyclops, can you hit it?

01:24:36.530 --> 01:24:39.700
<i>- [Cyclops] The rings are
too fast. I'll kill her.
- [Logan]Just shoot it.</i>

01:24:39.784 --> 01:24:42.078
- Storm, can you get me up there?
- I can't control it like that.

01:24:42.161 --> 01:24:45.039
- You could fly
right over the torch.
- Then let me go.

01:24:45.122 --> 01:24:49.502
If I don't make it,
then at least you can
still blast the damn thing.

01:24:50.711 --> 01:24:52.963
All right, do it.

01:24:53.047 --> 01:24:55.508
<i>Jean, use your power.
Try to steady him.</i>

01:24:56.926 --> 01:24:59.178
Hang on to something.

01:25:52.940 --> 01:25:55.067
Scott, wait.

01:26:25.681 --> 01:26:28.100
I have to.
Just wait.

01:26:29.935 --> 01:26:32.521
I have a shot.

01:26:32.605 --> 01:26:34.481
I'm taking it.

01:27:14.438 --> 01:27:16.357
Come on.

01:28:47.323 --> 01:28:50.075
Hey, this one's alive.
Let's get him out of here.

01:29:16.185 --> 01:29:18.103
Welcome back.

01:29:18.187 --> 01:29:21.231
<i>I knew you'd find
your way.</i>

01:29:21.315 --> 01:29:23.442
I had you to guide me.

01:29:25.652 --> 01:29:27.738
How did we do?

01:29:55.182 --> 01:29:57.935
Oh!
Oh, that tickles.

01:29:59.103 --> 01:30:01.021
Hey.

01:30:02.481 --> 01:30:04.400
Hey.

01:30:04.483 --> 01:30:07.778
How're you feeling?
Fantastic.

01:30:09.822 --> 01:30:12.199
That was
a brave thing you did.

01:30:13.617 --> 01:30:17.204
Did it work?
Yeah. She's fine.

01:30:18.872 --> 01:30:22.084
She took on a few
of your more charming
personality traits for a while.

01:30:22.167 --> 01:30:25.796
[ Chuckles,
Coughing ]
But we lived through it.

01:30:29.258 --> 01:30:32.177
I think she's
a little taken with you.

01:30:32.261 --> 01:30:36.682
Well, you can tell her
my heart belongs
to someone else.

01:30:41.061 --> 01:30:44.898
You know, you and I‒
How's the professor?

01:30:47.693 --> 01:30:50.696
He's good.
Good.

01:30:56.869 --> 01:31:01.123
There's an abandoned
military compound at Alkali Lake
in the Canadian Rockies,

01:31:01.206 --> 01:31:03.125
close to where
we found you.

01:31:03.208 --> 01:31:07.588
There's not much left,
but you might find
some answers.

01:31:10.090 --> 01:31:13.260
- Thank you.
- Are you going
to say good-bye to them?

01:31:16.096 --> 01:31:20.184
<i>[Man On TV]
The Mutant Registration Act
lost its main proponent today...</i>

01:31:20.267 --> 01:31:22.978
<i>with the dramatic reversal
of Senator Robert Kelly,</i>

01:31:23.061 --> 01:31:27.524
<i>who until this time had
provided the loudest voice in
the cry for mutant registration.</i>

01:31:27.608 --> 01:31:29.610
I was wrong
on this particular issue.

01:31:29.693 --> 01:31:33.030
And I hope in time
I may be forgiven.
Thank you.

01:31:33.113 --> 01:31:37.743
<i>The Mutant Registration Act
continues to draw support...
[Storm] Mystique.</i>

01:31:40.078 --> 01:31:43.373
<i>[Cyclops]
Son of a bitch.</i>

01:31:43.457 --> 01:31:47.085
<i>from many Parents Rights groups
who feel threatened...</i>

01:31:47.294 --> 01:31:49.213
<i>by unidentified mutants
in their school systems.</i>

01:31:49.296 --> 01:31:51.924
<i>In a related story,</i>

01:31:52.007 --> 01:31:56.428
<i>the body of Senator Kelly's
longtime aide, Henry Guyrich,
was found today.</i>

01:31:56.512 --> 01:32:01.767
<i>Preliminary coroner reports
seem to indicate that Guyrich
was mauled by a bear.</i>

01:32:01.850 --> 01:32:03.602
<i>[Rogue]
Hey.</i>

01:32:08.023 --> 01:32:11.485
You running again?
No, not really.

01:32:13.153 --> 01:32:16.281
I have some things
to take care of up north.

01:32:21.787 --> 01:32:23.956
I kind of like it.

01:32:27.125 --> 01:32:30.587
I don't want you to go.
[ Sniffles]

01:32:43.100 --> 01:32:45.102
I'll be back for this.

01:33:24.182 --> 01:33:26.727
Doesn't it ever wake you
in the middle of the night?

01:33:26.810 --> 01:33:29.646
The feeling that someday
they will pass
that foolish law...

01:33:29.730 --> 01:33:34.067
or one just like it
and come for you...

01:33:34.151 --> 01:33:37.029
and your children?

01:33:39.239 --> 01:33:41.533
It does, indeed.

01:33:46.830 --> 01:33:49.833
What do you do when
you wake up to that?

01:33:49.916 --> 01:33:53.086
I feel a great swell of pity
for the poor soul...

01:33:53.170 --> 01:33:56.840
who comes to that school
looking for trouble.

01:34:04.890 --> 01:34:07.517
Why do you come here,
Charles?

01:34:07.601 --> 01:34:10.604
Why do you ask questions
to which you already know
the answers?

01:34:10.687 --> 01:34:13.106
Oh, yes.

01:34:13.190 --> 01:34:15.567
Your continuing search
for hope.

01:34:26.620 --> 01:34:30.916
You know this
plastic prison of theirs
won't hold me forever.

01:34:30.999 --> 01:34:35.545
The war is still coming,
Charles, and I intend
to fight it...

01:34:35.629 --> 01:34:37.589
by any means necessary.

01:34:39.424 --> 01:34:42.928
And I will always
be there,

01:34:43.011 --> 01:34:44.930
old friend.
